      <hedline>
        <hl1>Ethical Politics, And Intellectual</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nora A Bailey letter disputes Frank Rich's August 5 Op-Ed column on Republican presidential nominee Gov George W Bush's leadership skills (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The G.O.P.'s Age of Aquarius,'' by Frank Rich (column, Aug. 5):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The G.O.P.'s Age of Aquarius,'' by Frank Rich (column, Aug. 5):</p>
        <p>Surely, Mr. Rich jests when he suggests that George W. Bush's leadership skills are evident in his ''taming'' of the far right during the Republican National Convention, something his father and Senator Bob Dole could not do. The reason is obvious: the far right never trusted the credentials of the two predecessors, whereas they have no doubt that George W. Bush is a true believer and will advance their policies once he is elected.</p>
        <p>What I had suspected before the convention was confirmed by the willingness of people like Dick Armey, Tom DeLay and Trent Lott to be muzzled during the convention.</p>
        <p>NORA A. BAILEY  Bethesda, Md., Aug. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
